cd /path/to/project → go to your project folder

git init → initialize Git locally

git config --global user.name "Your Name" → sets your name (for commits)

git config --global user.email "youremail@example.com" → sets your email

git add . → stages all files for commit

git commit -m "Initial commit" → creates the first commit

git remote add origin https://github.com/username/repo-name.git → connects your local repo to the GitHub remote

git branch -M main → ensures branch is named main

git push -u origin main → pushes your commit to GitHub and sets the upstream
